WE USED PEOBES TO CHECK IN PODS WHETHER THE CONTAINER IS READY OR NOT WE USE PROBES ARE 3 TYPES:


1) READINESS PROBES: ARE USED TO INDICATE WHEN CONTAINER IS REDAY TO REACIVE TRAFFIC

2) LIVENESS PROBES: ARE USED TO DETERMINE A CONTAINER IS STILL RUNNING AND RESPONDING  TO REQUESTS

3)STARTUP PROBES: IS USED TO WHETHER THE APPILICATION IN CONTAINER IS STARETD ARE NOT WE USE STARTUP PROBES


WE USE DELAY CONCEPT IN READINESS AND LIVNESS UNTIL THE APPLICATION IS RUNNING

FOR EX : ANY APPLICATION IN EKS WEITHER INCREASING OR DECREASING PODS IT WILL TAKE SOME TIME IT WILL TAKE SOME TIME

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

ex: 

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pod-1
  labels:
    test: live
spec:
  containers:
  - name: cont-1
    image: busybox
    args:
    - /bin/sh
    - -c
    - touch /tmp/healthy; sleep 1000

    livenessProbe:
      exec:  #Liveness probe runs a command (exec)
        command:
        - cat
        - /tmp/healthy
      initialDelaySeconds: 5  # Waits 5 seconds AFTER container starts, then begins checks
      periodSeconds: 5    # probe runs every 5 seconds
      timeoutSeconds: 30  # Probe waits max 30 seconds for command to finish
                          #If command times out → probe fails
